# Hybrid Explainer Strategy

- Do not fully replace interactive web lessons with video-only content.
- Choose explainer mode by learning objective:
  - Use web-first when learners must control pace (slider, teacher mode, step reveal, language switch).
  - Use Manim-first when core value is abstract intuition through continuous geometric/algebraic transformation.
  - Use hybrid by default: short Manim segments for hard intuition, web UI for verification and interaction.
- Keep learner-facing conclusions consistent across all channels (video, solution text, validation matrix).
- Prefer reversible architecture decisions: add Manim as an asset layer, not as a platform replacement.
- For children-facing content, prioritize correctness and clarity over visual complexity.
